Q-hum sbom generate karte hai fir uske report ko scan karte hai ? and if yes then which tool and why ?

A-
Process generally aisa hota hai:

SBOM generate karna – pehle tum apne project ka SBOM (Software Bill of Materials) banao, jisme sab dependencies, libraries, licenses, versions ki detail hoti hai.

Tools: Syft, CycloneDX plugin, SPDX tools etc.

SBOM ko scan karna – fir us SBOM ko vulnerability scanners se scan karte hain taaki known CVEs, outdated packages, aur risky licenses detect ho sake.

Tools:

Grype (agar Syft se SBOM banaya hai toh best pair hai)

Trivy (SBOM + container + code sab scan kar sakta hai)

Dependency-Track (CycloneDX SBOM analyze karta hai aur continuously monitor bhi karta hai)

🔑 Why ye tools?

Syft + Grype → lightweight, fast, aur CLI-based (DevSecOps pipelines me easy).

Trivy → all-in-one (SBOM generate bhi karega, scan bhi).

Dependency-Track → enterprise-level monitoring, dashboard-based, continuous SBOM analysis.

👉 Simple workflow:
Syft → SBOM.json → Grype/Trivy → Vulnerability Report

